#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rrahit Revealing and Hiding Input Tabs #!N 
#!EC #!N #!N Most of the tools have more input tabs 
than are displayed when a tool icon is initially displayed. For 
example, the Isosurface module has six inputs, but when an Isosurface 
tool icon is initially placed on the canvas, only three input 
tabs are displayed. The displayed tabs represent those that are most 
frequently used. #!N #!N To reveal the hidden input tabs: #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the tool 
icon by clicking on it. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Select the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Reveal All Tabs #!EF option from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF 
pull-down menu. (You can also use the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+L #!EF accelerator 
key.) #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N Once the input 
tabs have been revealed, they can be hidden. #!N #!N To 
hide input tabs: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 
1. Select the tool icon by clicking on it. #!N #!I30 
#!N 2. Select the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Hide All Tabs #!EF option from 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF pull-down menu. (You can also use the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+H #!EF accelerator key.) #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N 
#!N Hiding input tabs in this way will cause all tabs 
that are not connected to another module to be hidden. #!N 
#!N If you wish to hide or reveal individual inputs, use 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   hide #!EF toggle button in the Configuration dialog box 
(see  #!Linsect,dxall347 h Inputs Section  #!EL  ). #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
#!N  #!Lcompdi,dxall351 h Using the Compute Module Configuration Dialog Box  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
